While there appears to be an experimental vaccine that can reduce mortality from Ebola, no drug has yet been found that has been clearly demonstrated to be suitable for the treatment of the existing infection.
A cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, was initially shown to be promising in the field, but formal studies have revealed a lower than expected efficacy in preventing deaths.
In the PALM study, ZMapp was used as a control, whereas the scientists used it as a reference and compared it to the other three therapies.
USA Gymnastics supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and recognizes the absolute need on the part of the Olympic community to work towards creating a safe environment for all of its athletes.
We agree with the USOC that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, and of their sport, can be best served by bringing about a significant change within our organisation, and not by decertification.
USA Gymnastics has sponsored an independent investigation to understand how it was possible that an abuse of the dimensions described with such courage by those who managed to survive Larry Nassar remained hidden for so long, and is willing to implement any necessary or appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC share the same objective: to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible, so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a trustworthy, positive and responsible environment.
In the 1960s, Brzezinski was a counselor to John F. Kennedy and later to Lyndon B. Johnson.
In the course of the 1976 elections, Carter advised on foreign policy matters and then assumed the role of National Security Adviser (NSA) from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
As a member of the NSA, he collaborated with Carter in the diplomatic management of international affairs, including the 1978 Camp David Accords, the normalization of relations between China and the United States in the late 1970s, the Iranian Revolution (which led to the 1979 hostage crisis in Iran) and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan in 1979.
