The 802.11n standard can operate in both the 2.4GHz and the 5.0GHz bands.
Since the base station has a dual radio, this will allow it to be backward compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g.
The speeds of 802.11n are considerably higher than those of the previous versions, with a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbps.
